This paper is about pregroup models of natural language, which are commonly used in computational linguistics and natural language processing. The paper discusses the relationship between pregroup models and Compositional Distributional Semantics, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the formalization of pregroup models in algebraic, categorical, and graphical terms, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of information flow in natural language, which is relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
